{
  "doc_id": "60830",
  "text": "Approximately 10% of PSP patients have a positive family history [CITATION_1] , with an autosomal dominant inheritance with incomplete penetrance, X-linked recessive or polygenic inheritance [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Mutations in the folliculin gene have been identified in individuals with familial PSP [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] , but the genetic aetiology of sporadic PSP remains unknown since there are no published genetic association studies.",
